  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nTo mitigate DNS rebinding attacks, the REST API should validate the `Host` header matches one of the whitelisted hostnames.\r\n\r\nThis should be similar to the Besu `--host-whitelist`: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Interact/APIs/API/#host-whitelist although I don't believe we need to support the special \"all\" or \"none\" magic values `--rest-api-host-whitelist=` would be the equivalent of \"none\" and just use `*` as the only value for `all`.",
